ANC leader Musalia Mudavadi has asked DPP Noordin Haji to order fresh investigations into procurement of the multi-billion leased medical equipment scheme by the government, terming it as a scandal. He said the scheme had burdened counties with massive debts and exploited the sick. Mudavadi in a statement on Saturday said that the profiteers of the scheme stole funds through the initial lease procurement where the cost was grossly inflated. Click here for the latest political news